<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,581,767]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,555,581,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Family diagnosis (adult female).</emphasis>
Podospermal monogynaspid 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G.Canestrini" authorityYear="1891" box="[906,1070,581,607]" class="Arachnida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Mesostigmata</taxonomicName>
with a holodorsal shield. Sternal shield with a maximum of three pairs of setae; metasternal setae inserted on soft skin or on separate metasternal plates; epigynal shield with one pair of setae or none. Anal shield with one pair of para-anal setae and a post-anal seta, occasionally surrounded by sclerotised skin that mimics a ventri-anal shield. Tibia I with four or five dorsal setae; tibia I and genu I with one anterolateral seta (1 3/2 2/1 2 or 1 2/1 2/1 1).
</paragraph>
